<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-750-930  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 750 930.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  August 17 1990 n1493* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Grid's 80386SX laptop has tilt bar cursor driver, built-in Windows3. (Grid Systems Inc.'s Gridcase 1550sx) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Grid Systems Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Grid Systems GRiDCase 1550sx (Portable computer) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionLaptop Computers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>GRID'S 80386SX LAPTOP HAS TILT BAR CURSOR DRIVER,andM;BUILT-IN WINDOWS 3andM;As well as having Microsoft Windows 3.0 installed on the capacious 60Mb harddisk, Tandy Corp's subsidiary GRiD Systems Inc's new lap-top dispenses withthe irritating mouse, replacing it with an &quot;Isopoint&quot; tilting bar to controlthe cursor, installed immediately below the space bar on the keyboard.andP;  Thenew machine, launched yesterday in Boston, also uses the 20MHz version of the80386SX chip to put it close to the top in terms of laptop performance - butwith prices starting at $6,300, the new GRiDcase 1550sx is not cheap.andO;Weighing in at 12 lbs, the machine has 2Mb of memory, 3.5&quot; floppy, the harddisk has 16mS access time and the thing comes with black-on-white liquidcrystal diode display with VGA graphics; the battery life is about threehours.andP;  Options include 120Mb disk, built-in 2,400 bps modem, and arechargeable battery; it is planned to be available from next month.andO;</TEXT></DOC>